**Event Title:** CON - AppSec Challenge

**Organizer:** @Sketrik & @l4wke

**Event Description:** 
- The challenge involves finding and fixing vulnerabilities in source code. 
- Participants compete against each other to be the first to fix all vulnerabilities in a web application, clone the repo, fix vulnerabilities, and submit their code for scoring.
- This year's application consists of several microservices each written in different programming languages.

**How to Participate:**
- Clone the repository, find and fix vulnerabilities, ensure unit tests pass locally, and submit results to the scoring engine.
- The application has been developed in multiple programming languages, allowing participants to start with something familiar and gradually challenge themselves with new languages.

**Key Competition Details:**
- **Contest Hours:**
  - Start: Tuesday, 12 PM
  - End: Friday, 9 AM
- **Booth Hours:**
  - Tuesday: 10:30 AM – 5:00 PM
  - Wednesday: 10:30 AM – 5:00 PM
  - Thursday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM
  - Friday: 9:00 AM – 10:00 AM

**Rules:**
- Hacking the site or submission mechanism is forbidden; participants can only test on their own hosts.
- Limit changes to files specified in the provided packaging script.
- File uploads are restricted to less than 4 MB.
- Submissions can only be made once per user every 5 minutes; duplicate submissions will not be scored.
- Prizes awarded at the awards ceremony for the top scorers.
- For support, participants can interact with the AppSec Community or reach out directly to @sketrik.

**Resources:**
- Additional assistance can be found in the AppSec community’s Discord for those needing help starting. 

**Contact Information:**
- For inquiries regarding the event or support, participants are encouraged to visit the AppSec community’s platform. 

**Event Website:** [SAINTCON Event Page](https://saintcon.org/con-appsec-challenge/)